					<marginalia_text>
						Vir serius, qui pendet &agrave; Seipso; et homo foelix. Nam mihi crede,
						credendum Nemini: et cum maxim&egrave; opus amicis, amicus est nullus.
					</marginalia_text>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				A man who depends on himself is a serious and happy person. But, trust me: believe in 
				no one; and especially when friends are needed. A friend is nothing.
			</translation>
